In addition to within site variation, there is considerable among population variation, with almost every population displaying some unique feature. Out of this diversity I describe a couple of variants. Variant 1 (Figure 69
G-I
) occurs at several sites in Guatemala (e.g. Biotopo Quetzal, 
Purulha
). It is similar to the type form, but has a bulging postpetiole and longer gastral pilosity. Variant 2 (Figure 69
J-L
) occurs at La Union in Guatemala, with similar-looking specimens at sites in Honduras. Compared to the type form it is smaller and has the suberect layer of gastral pilosity noticeably thickened. Until there is evidence of sympatry, I treat all of this variation as intraspecific.
